The '''Nicolas Appert Award''' is awarded by the [[Chicago]] Section of the [[Institute of Food Technologists]] for preeminence in and contributions to the field of [[food technology]].<ref>http://www.ift.org/membership/awards-and-recognition/achievement-awards/nicolas-appert-award.aspx</ref> The award has been given annually since 1942 and is named after [[Nicolas Appert]], the French inventor of airtight food preservation. Award winners receive a bronze medal with a front view of Appert and a $5000 [[honorarium]]. This is considered one of the highest honors in food technology.<ref>http://chicagoift.org/nicolas-appert-award.php</ref>
